Text: Go and be finlesss somewhere elssse!
My curse will consume you from within!

In life and in death
I serve Ronka...

Forever bound to this
place by sacred pact...

For the empire...
For the emperor...
I am sure thisss is the place.
Those benthos beat us to it...

What happened here?
Were you attacked?

Hahaha! Oh, you
righteous fools are
too easy to snare.

You're just so
<i>predictable<i>. Ha...
Haha... Ahahaha!
You will never belong here. Not like us.
Keep your peace. It won't save you.

That could've gone
much worse, if you
hadn't come along.

I ought to
have known better.

Nightshade never tires
of dirty tricks.

Get moving. We
don't have the time
to waste here.

You made a
hash of it, then?

Look, we had
the same problem
with the strongholds...

The arrogance of
the Crystarium's ignorant
knows no bounds.

Well, we'll have to
see to that.

Let's make sure
they get what's
coming to them.

These lands were
always ours. Now
more than ever.
The finlesss ones and their pathetic friends shhhall perish!
The mighty one will sssup on your fleshhh!
You would unleash that evil upon the Tempessst!?

You go on ahead.
I will hold them off here!
I do believe it's time that I took center stage!
Have care. We know not what lies within...
Perhaps there's a pattern to their movements.
I must ask that you refrain from wandering...

Oh, I wouldn't dream of it!
La la la♪

It'll be finished when I say
it's finished, and I say it's
not finished! At least not yet.

Well, let me know when it is!
I don't want to miss when we
crush the Tholls!

Who goes there!?
A Tholl spy!?

Help! Someone! Anyone!
I'm too short to die!
Not the beard! Not the beard!

They've got us by the beard!
To the hills!

That will teach you to
stick your beard in Gogg
business!

You won't see me again!
I swear it!

These legs can only carry us
so far. We must fight!
The battle is lost! Fall back, fall back!

I knew it! The Goggs are
up to no good!

Any friend of the Tholls
is an enemy of ours!
Let seep sorrow into your heart.

Our secret weapon is
almost complete!

You may have defeated us
today, but tomorrow shall be ours!

Tell me your plan or I'll
have your helm!
Not if you're rotting in our gaol!

You wouldn't stab a dwarf
in the back now, would you?

Run today, live to
fight another day!
You are out of your element!
Wake up! Wake up, damn you!
I don't think I've ever seen anywhere so peaceful and serene.
Ha ha! I will give it some thought.

Oh, Gridania is a wonderful
place indeed! You should
stay a while.
I hope Editha is all right!
Please, take good care of her.

If you require my assistance,
do not hesitate to ask!
Editha, you mustn't run off like that again!

Do you know who could
be behind these attacks?
Yes, I think we've gathered that much...
Glad to see the threat of assassination has done little to dampen your mood.

Are you alright?
You've gone pale...

Ah...
Your eyes tell the tale.
We were too slow to save them!

We free their souls.
That is all we can do...

I feel my skin prickling.
What is this boiling aether...?
The manor house is just up ahead!

We are close...
Be on your guard!
As is the source of this suffocating aether...

The sheer power...
I can sense its strength from here!

Gods...
This must be the Warden!
...We stand in the presence of a Lightwarden.
Aye, this is the true scourge of Lakeland!

Are they preparing
for an assault?

Everyone at the ready!
We strike first!
How noble of you to come to us!

We'll put you
out of your misery!
Now you see the futility of the good.

The only glory
is in sin!

Only the wicked
will walk these lands!

There are too
many of them!

Only the elves
truly know this world
we have created.

You were never
going to succeed.

We just don't
have the numbers...

What will become
of Lakeland now?
Echoes, I think. But there is something strange about them.
Bows, with me! We have work to do!
It seems that they are diseased.
We must cull them before the sickness can spread.
We have allowed too many of them to escape...
Perhaps we will find some of them on our patrol.
Bows! It is time to leave!
Those crawlers must be what is spreading the disease!
My thoughts exactly. Sisters, you know what to do.
That should put a stop to the disease.
We are running dangerously low on arrows, though.
I suggest that we go and gather feathers for flights.
We let too many of them get away.
These tarichuks are tougher than they look...
I had best stop there. No point dying for a bunch of feathers.
This should suffice. Your assistance is much appreciated.
That is enough for the time being.
I will take those feathers off of your hands!
Bring me as many feathers as you can. It matters not how you get them.
Keep your eyes peeled for trouble.
They are attacking the ancient guardian!
To think that the ancient guardian could be defeated...
There is little more we can do here. Let us return.
It seems the danger has passed.
Come. We must report this to the others.
Did you hear that? It sounded like a roar...
If that is what I think it is, we must hurry!
Many a sister has died fighting that beast.
It is heading towards the village!
Quickly, there is no time to lose!
We have it running for its life. Now is our chance!
Sisters, we shall fight to the last!
This must be one of its defenses.
Do not get too close, sisters!
Your reign of terror has lasted long enough.
May the fallen rest in peace.
For now. Though Tojil is slain, our work is never done.
Let us return to the village.
We cannot allow the disease to spread!
Get them away from the ancient guardian!
Those that threaten the forest must perish!

Careful, mortal!
The bees are
everywhere...
It's not much, but I'm not going over there...

In fact, let's leave.
Quickly. Yes.

I'll just start
backing away slowly...

Let's get the
herbs and go.

Please...
My friend─he'll die
without these!

But you'll have
so much more
fun with us!

Now we can get
what we came for.

I can't go back
without the nectar...

At last, I can
go home and─
I am never doing nectar duty again...

If I didn't need that
nectar, I swear...

Now I can get to the
Bookman's Shelves.

They do look
ever so peaceful...

...and that won't do,
will it now?

Hmm, I believe
it is time we
took our leave.

We would thank
you for the fun...

...if only you
weren't quite
so dull!

I daresay we
shall find better
sport elsewhere.

They're doubtless off
to trouble some
other poor soul.
I'll keep an eye on them.

We shall have
to find out!

A wee bit of
this, and...yes!

Oh dear. Are
you quite alright?

I say! That's
rather painful, sir!

I suppose we
have our answer.

It wasn't even a
funny prank! Unacceptable!

Perhaps this fellow
can be of assistance.

Oh, dear, would
you look at that...
It will take ages to collect more...

Our persistent pixie.
What a lovely surprise!
You stop this nonsense at once!

Oho, they seem
to be keeping up.
Shall we give them a chance?

A magicked tree?
What do you take me for?
If we were to be honest...
But there is time for sport yet!
You are an entertaining lot indeed.
Oh, no. Not yet, I think!

But perhaps if you
follow us south...
But I do hope they'll do better than a tree.
We are so pleased to have you here...

Much more entertaining
than we expected.

If only I could say
the same for you.

You haven't seen
the half of us yet!
Ha! Fuath tricks don't scare me!

Now I teach you
a thing or two!
But wouldn't the Bookman's Shelves be a more appropriate venue?

I thought you
might say that!
...and it turns out we're not quite done...
Now, if you'll just come this way...
At this point, it seems only fair to mention...
We'll have great fun either way, of course.

I don't doubt that.
You have terrible taste.
While there's still fun to be had?
But what a loss it was!

We really must do
this again sometime!
It seems we are the victors!
We thank you for the diversion...
You could at least try to fight back.

A bit more savagery,
if you please.
